data.body:
Would like to be able to apply a transition on a TextEditorDecorationType . Something like this:

```
var flashDecorationType = vscode.window.createTextEditorDecorationType({
  backgroundColor: 'rgba(100,200,100,0.5)',
  transition: 'backgroundColor 1s ease-out'
});
```

- VSCode Version: 1.3.0 Insider 2016-07-01T05:29:54.785Z
- OS Version: Mac 10.11

Steps to Reproduce:
1. take the language server node example and adapt it as follows

```
capabilities: {
            // Tell the client that the server works in FULL text document sync mode
            textDocumentSync: documents.syncKind,
            // Tell the client that the server support code complete
            completionProvider: {
                resolveProvider: true
            },
            hoverProvider : true
        }
```

```
connection.onHover(
    (p : TextDocumentPositionParams) : Hover => {
        console.log(p.position.character);

        return {
            contents: "xxxxx" + p.position.character,
            range : {
                start : {line: 0, character: 0},
                end : {line: 0, character: 10}
            }
        }

    }   )
;
```
1.  using the hover and hovering in the middle of the first character gives offset 1 instead of 0
